{
  "doc_id": "31123",
  "text": "Comparison of the complete 16s rRNA gene sequence of M . tuberculosis with that of M . bovis [CITATION_1] revealed one difference, the insertion/deletion of a C residue located in the hairpin loop region of helix 47 [nucleotides 2022-2104, Fig. 2 ; nucleotides 1401-1483 in the inferred 16s rRNA sequence ( Fig. 3) ]. The sequence for the hairpin loop is SCUCG3' in M . tuberculosis (see also [CITATION_2] ) compared with 5'CUG3' for M . bovis, as reported previously (Suzuki et al., 1988a) .",
